# MILESTONE** — round-number landmark in taxonomy growth.
#
# This completion OPENS Axis 20 (YAML PARSING) — the 20th documented
# cross-language CLI library axis.  Axis 20 covers the cross-language
# pattern of "library used by CLIs to parse and emit YAML 1.1 / 1.2
# documents" — applicable to Kubernetes manifest tools (kubectl,
# helm, kustomize), CI/CD config parsers (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI,
# CircleCI), application config readers (most Rails/Spring/Phoenix-
# style frameworks), OpenAPI spec parsers (this CLI), Ansible
# playbooks, and any CLI consuming structured YAML input.
#
#   Axis 20 (YAML PARSING) variants:
#     - serde_yaml (dtolnay/serde-yaml) — R669 (THIS) — Rust
#       serde-integrated YAML; YAML 1.2 + 1.1 support; document-
#       stream parsing; serde_yaml::Value untyped access; anchor/
#       alias preservation; retired 2024 but installed-base
#       canonical; David Tolnay / dtolnay ecosystem
