#
# Cross-language Axis 20 design analysis:
#   The "YAML parser" abstraction is non-stdlib in all three
#   languages — none of Rust / Go / Node ship YAML support in
#   their standard libraries.  Each language has competing
#   implementations:
#     - Rust:  serde_yaml (retired, still dominant), serde-yml,
#               serde-yaml-bw, saphyr, yaml-rust
#     - Go:    gopkg.in/yaml.v3 (Canonical), go-yaml (legacy),
#               goccy/go-yaml (alternative)
#     - Node:  js-yaml (nodeca), yaml (eemeli), yaml-ast-parser,
#               yamljs
#   serde_yaml dominates Rust by sheer installed base + serde
#   integration; gopkg.in/yaml.v3 is the recommended Go YAML
#   library (used by kubectl, helm, viper); js-yaml is the
#   default Node YAML library (used by Webpack, ESLint, GitHub
#   Actions tooling, etc.).  Each is a clean Axis 20 pick.
